				<div class="before-after-list">
					<ul>
						<li>Just to create a new message, users had to navigate through the entire company directory.</li>
						<li>Looking for my coworker, Sam would require scrolling through 300+ names first.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="col-md-5">
				<div class="screenshots-before-after">
					<img src="/images/projects/glip-project/8-create_team_2.png">
					<h4>AFTER</h4>
				</div>
				<div class="before-after-list">
					<ul>
						<li>Creating a team required at least 3 taps: first to give the team a name, then to select who could join the team, and finally to select members to add to the team.</li>
						<li>Adding members to a team required scrolling through a long list of contacts to find a person and add them.</li>
						<li>There was no visible place to see who I had added to the team, without scrolling up and down to see my selections.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
